  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nWas confirmed by Pedro on [Discord](https://discord.com/channels/624634427930312714/928646594314784859/1129000866406477835)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nUnread `COUNTERS` on the chat/communities tabs should be only displayed:\r\n- when a mention or reply is received in community/group chat\r\n- for any message in 1-1 chat\r\n\r\nFor all other cases unread `DOTS` should be displayed on the tabs\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n<img width=\"430\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-09-22 at 16 52 44\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/67952253/66337f54-ca9e-4472-ac14-d5c47d14e114\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Join a group chat\r\n2. Open the chat home screen\r\n3. Recieve a regular message in the group\r\n4. Check the unread indicator on the Chat tab\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 22/09\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
